radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated to 12 mm, contains fluid and air, as well as a 5-mm appendicolith. The appendix wall is mildly hyperenhancing. Stranding is observed in the surrounding fat. No evidence of extraluminal air, abscess, retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy, free abdominal fluid, abdominal wall hernia, or pneumoperitoneum.
